RIYADH: Dubai Multi Commodities Center has appointed American commercial real estate services and investment firm CBRE Group as a leasing advisor for Dubaiâ€™s new 340-meter Uptown Tower. CBRE will also provide strategic marketing for the building in its pre-leasing campaign. The new development is the first super-tall tower to be located in the Uptown Dubai district, and is projected to be one of the most significant projects in the UAE. The 400,000 sq ft building with Grade A offices is expected to be completed in the third quarter of 2022. The tower will serve as an option for luxury living, a home for leading firms, entertainment outlets, luxurious food and beverage options, and exclusive retail stores.